parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the seatbelt tensioner is faulty
the cable reel (clockspring) fails
and the airbag indicator stays on even after repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair or replace Takata airbags can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the recall repair is not completed
and the part is not available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt tensioner can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the seatbelt tensioner is faulty
and the airbag does not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to slip out of gear, resulting in a loss of control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips out of gear
the vehicle hesitates or refuses to shift
grinding or whining noises
and the engine RPMs surge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and grinding or whining noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control can cause the vehicle to suddenly accelerate or decelerate, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control drops out unexpectedly
and the vehicle accelerates or decelerates suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The difficulty in engaging reverse gear can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: Grinding or whining noises when engaging reverse gear
and difficulty shifting into reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission judder can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The transmission judders or vibrates when accelerating from a stop
and grinding or whining noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is unable to be controlled.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
often when the brake pedal is depressed
and the engine RPM increases. The brakes may not respond or may be ineffective in stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty speedometer can lead to accidents or traffic violations, as the driver may not be aware of their actual speed.
symptoms: The speedometer does not function or registers an incorrect speed
which can cause confusion and potentially lead to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is unable to stop in time.
symptoms: The brakes do not respond or are ineffective in stopping the vehicle
often accompanied by unintended acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and transmission problems can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is unable to shift gears properly.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
or the transmission fails to shift gears properly.
